text: Adolf Fredrik Church () is a church building in the town of Stockholm in Sweden. It belongs to the Church of Sweden. It was opened on 27 November 1774. In its graveyard, former Swedish prime ministers Hjalmar Branting and Olof Palme have been buried. == References == ==Other websites== Category:Church of Sweden churches Category:Churches in Stockholm Category:18th-century buildings and structures
title: Adolf Fredrik Church
